RACE.FOOTNOTES: DOT COM DREAMIN settled in stalking position along the inside up the backstretch, cut the corner and launched an inside bid heading into the lane, roused forward to take command nearing the eighth pole, edged ahead to a clear lead and held firm. PRIDEOFDIXIECREED got bumped between rivals at the start and raced in the back, picked up the tempo and edged up closer three wide late on the turn, launched a four wide bid heading into the stretch run, steadily advanced down the lane and had to settle for second best. STAR OF MINE sped to the lead at the start and set the early pace, held firm over pursuers around the turn then hustled up two wide into the lane, got collared by the eventual winner approaching the eighth pole and weakened to show. MIDNIGHT RULES was unhurried and settled in the back, saved ground on the rail around the turn, hustled up along the inside through the lane and improved position. COLORFUL NATIVE was forwardly placed racing just off the early leader, continued in strong contention near the quarter pole, came three wide into the lane and steadily weakened. IT'S ALL ABOUT JOE raced in range up the backstretch, failed to advance when called upon around the turn, came three wide into the lane and gave way.

RACE.FOOTNOTES: HOPING FOR A RING raced four wide heading into the first turn and edged closer entering the backstretch, pressed the pace three wide up the backstretch, remained up close still unleashed late on the far turn, given cue turning for home, dueled for command with UNDECODED down the lane, fought on determinedly under firm handling and edged by in final strides. UNDECODED saved ground and grabbed the lead heading into the first turn, set a pressured pace on the inside up the backstretch, held a slim lead around the far turn, took on the challenge from HOPING FOR A RING entering the lane, dueled from the inside position and held a slight edge, fought back gamely but could not hold off the winner approaching the wire. SIMONA'S CHOICE was away in good order and raced three wide entering the first turn, settled in good position stalking the close knit top trio up the backstretch, roused for more mid-way around the far turn, swung four wide into the lane then angled to the inside and stayed on for a share. SHE'S FIRE AND ICE was forwardly placed racing two wide around the first turn, pressed the pace up the backstretch, came up empty entering the far turn, retreated and jogged in.

RACE.RACE_TEXT: PRAIRIE MEADOWS RACE 7 5 1/2F Dirt CR: 57. Maiden Claiming Purse 25101. FOR REGISTERED STATE BRED MAIDENS, THREE, FOUR, FIVE, AND SIX YEARS OLD. Three Year Olds, 118 lbs.; Older, 124 lbs. Claiming Price $30,000.

TEMPLE CITY RUN was not too far back in early stages, coaxed two to three wide around the turn, hustled along four wide into the lane, kicked in gear, accelerated down the lane and got up late to capture place. MACH SWEDE broke sharp from the outside then conceded position to a duo, sat well placed tracking just off the embattled pair in early stages, let out a notch leaving the backstretch, engaged HIGGAM for the lead, dueled around the turn, continued to battle for command into deep stretch then got outkicked when a duo surged by late. HIGGAM dueled outside of BABYS TIME TO SING in opening stages then took on the challenge of MACH SWEDE leaving the backstretch, battled for command around the turn, continued to battle back into deep stretch then got outfinished in final stages. COUNTY JAIL raced off the early pace, swung four to five wide into the lane and had a mild improve. ESPE'S GUY was not too far back in early stages along the inside, chased two wide around the turn and failed to move on in the lane. SARAH'S BOY BLUE raced off the early front runners, saved ground around the turn and lacked a rally in the lane. BABYS TIME TO SING dueled long the inside of HIGGAM for the lead in opening stages, could not match strides past the three eighths pole but remained in contention, ran on into the upper stretch then came up empty in the final furlong. GLOME raced in the back throughout.
